# DevMentor / Terminal Depths — Cursor Project Rules

## What This Project Is
A VS Code-native mentorship platform (DevMentor) that embeds a full cyberpunk terminal RPG (Terminal Depths). The game runs as a FastAPI server, teaches real developer skills through gameplay, and is designed to be extended by AI agents.

## Critical Architecture Rules

### NEVER DO THESE:
- Rewrite `app/game_engine/commands.py` wholesale — it's 30,000+ lines, surgical edits only
- Use `_info()` helper — it's undefined at module scope. Will crash.
- Create duplicate `_cmd_` methods — grep first to check if it exists
- Use port 7337 for Replit (that's Docker only) — use port 5000

### ALWAYS DO THESE:
- Use the correct helpers: `_line(text, type)`, `_dim(text)`, `_ok(text)`, `_err(text)`, `_sys(text)`, `_lore(text)`
- Register new commands in the aliases dict around line 1415 in commands.py
- Create a man page in `docs/commands/<name>.md` for every new command
- Test with: `curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/api/game/command -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"session_id":"cursor-test","command":"<cmd>"}'`
- Run syntax check after any commands.py edit: `python3 -c "import ast; ast.parse(open('app/game_engine/commands.py').read())"`

